adjectives.description: fuscous (comparative more fuscous, superlative most fuscous)

entries.meaning: Dark in color, dark-hued; dusky, swarthy.
examples: ‘Fresh, fresh, fresh,’ one commented in deep bass on the departing soldier, and the other nodded assent, though in that cave of spoiled air and fuscous lamplight the word ‘fresh’ was misleading […].
